{"questionId":"9073124","questionHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Light of wavelength <em>λ</em> is normally incident on a diffraction grating of spacing 3<em>λ</em>. What is the angle between the two second-order maxima?</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">D.&nbsp; &gt;90° so no second orders appear</span></span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9073124","referenceCode":"19N.1.HL.TZ0.28","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Light of wavelength λ is normally incident on a diffraction grating of spacing 3λ. What is the angle between the two second-order maxima? A. sin-123 B. sin-143 C. 2sin-123 D. >90° ","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"28","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena","9.3 – Interference","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}